content: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?> <metadata>  <idinfo>   <citation>    <citeinfo>     <origin>U.S. Geological Survey (USGS), EROS Data Center</origin>     <pubdate>1999</pubdate>     <title>National Elevation Dataset (NED)</title>     <edition>1</edition>     <geoform>raster digital data</geoform>     <pubinfo>      <pubplace>Sioux Falls, SD</pubplace>      <publish>U.S. Geological Survey</publish>     </pubinfo>     <onlink>http://www.KansasGIS.org</onlink>     <ftname Sync="TRUE">ned.txt</ftname></citeinfo>   </citation>   <descript>    <abstract> The U.S. Geological Survey has developed a National Elevation Database (NED).  The NED is a seamless mosaic of best-available elevation data. The 7.5-minute elevation data for the conterminous United States are the primary initial source data.  In addition to the availability of complete 7.5-minute data, efficient processing methods were developed to filter production artifacts in the existing data, convert to the NAD83 datum, edge-match, and fill slivers of missing data at quadrangle seams. One of the effects of the NED processing steps is a much-improved base of elevation data for calculating slope and hydrologic derivatives. </abstract>    <purpose> Geospatial elevation data are utilized by the scientific and resource management communities for global change research, hydrologic modeling, resource monitoring, mapping, and visualization applications. </purpose>    <langdata Sync="TRUE">en</langdata></descript>   <timeperd>    <timeinfo>     <rngdates>      <begdate>19990201</begdate>      <enddate>unknown</enddate>     </rngdates>    </timeinfo>    <current>publication date</current>   </timeperd>   <status>    <progress>In work</progress>    <update>As needed</update>   </status>   <spdom>    <bounding>     <westbc>-102.5</westbc>     <eastbc>-94.6</eastbc>     <northbc>40.0</northbc>     <southbc>37.0</southbc>    </bounding>   </spdom>   <keywords>    <theme>     <themekt>GCMD Parameter Keywords</themekt>     <themekey>elevation</themekey>     <themekey>EARTH SCIENCE</themekey>     <themekey>LAND SURFACE</themekey>     <themekey>TOPOGRAPHY</themekey>     <themekey>LANDFORMS</themekey>     <themekey>TERRAIN ELEVATION</themekey>     <themekey>1-DEGREE DEM</themekey>     <themekey>2-ARC-SECOND DEM</themekey>     <themekey>7.5-MINUTE DEM</themekey>     <themekey>CARTOGRAPHY</themekey>     <themekey>DEM</themekey>     <themekey>DIGITAL ELEVATION MODEL</themekey>     <themekey>DIGITAL MAPPING</themekey>     <themekey>EDC</themekey>     <themekey>EROS</themekey>     <themekey>GEODATA</themekey>     <themekey>GIS</themekey>     <themekey>MAPPING</themekey>     <themekey>RASTER</themekey>     <themekey>USGS</themekey>    </theme>    <place>     <placekt>GCMD Location Keywords</placekt>     <placekey>Kansas</placekey>     <placekey>NORTH AMERICA</placekey>     <placekey>UNITED STATES</placekey>     <placekey>UNITED STATES OF AMERICA</placekey>    </place>   </keywords>   <accconst>None</accconst>   <useconst> None.
